    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "John",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 8,
        "summary": "The woman taken in adultery is brought before Christ\u2014Christ is the Light of the world\u2014He again proclaims that He is the Messiah\u2014The true children of Abraham believe in Christ\u2014Jesus says, Before Abraham was I, Jehovah.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Jesus went unto the mount of Olives.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And early in the morning he came again into the temple, and all the people came unto him; and he sat down, and taught them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 26:55; Luke 21:37.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p2",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the scribes and Pharisees brought unto him a woman taken in adultery; and when they had set her in the midst,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Woman.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Adulterer.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They say unto him, Master, this woman was taken in adultery, in the very act.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Now Moses in the law commanded us, that such should be stoned: but what sayest thou?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lev. 20:10.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "This they said, tempting him, that they might have to accuse him. But Jesus stooped down, and with his finger wrote on the ground, as though he heard them not.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Teaching Mode of.",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 115
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 102
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 159
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "So when they continued asking him, he lifted up himself, and said unto them, He that is without sin among you, let him first cast a stone at her.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 14:5 (1\u20135).",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 99
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 17:7.",
                        "start": 119,
                        "end": 124
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gossip.",
                        "start": 132,
                        "end": 137
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And again he stooped down, and wrote on the ground.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they which heard it, being convicted by their own conscience, went out one by one, beginning at the eldest, even unto the last: and Jesus was left alone, and the woman standing in the midst.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Conscience.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 53
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 112,
                        "end": 116
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "When Jesus had lifted up himself, and saw none but the woman, he said unto her, Woman, where are those thine accusers? hath no man condemned thee?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "She said, No man, Lord. And Jesus said unto her, Neither do I condemn thee: go, and sin no more.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Benevolence; Mercy.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 42:25.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 87
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0John 8:11 \u2026 more. And the woman glorified God from that hour, and believed on his name.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then spake Jesus again unto them, saying, I am the light of the world: he that followeth me shall not walk in darkness, but shall have the light of life.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Jn. 1:5. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Light of the World; Light [noun]; Light of Christ.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking in Darkness.",
                        "start": 102,
                        "end": 106
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Darkness, Spiritual.",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 118
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p12",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The Pharisees therefore said unto him, Thou bearest record of thyself; thy record is not true.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Jesus answered and said unto them, Though I bear record of myself, yet my record is true: for I know whence I came, and whither I go; but ye cannot tell whence I come, and whither I go.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 16:28.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 107
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 9:29.",
                        "start": 153,
                        "end": 159
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye judge after the flesh; I judge no man.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 12:47.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And yet if I judge, my judgment is true: for I am not alone, but I and the Father that sent me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Judge.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Judgment.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 8:29; 16:32.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "It is also written in your law, that the testimony of two men is true.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Witness.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I am one that bear witness of myself, and the Father that sent me beareth witness of me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Godhead; God the Father, Elohim.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Witness of the Father.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then said they unto him, Where is thy Father? Jesus answered, Ye neither know me, nor my Father: if ye had known me, ye should have known my Father also.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 14:7.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 112
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "These words spake Jesus in the treasury, as he taught in the temple: and no man laid hands on him; for his hour was not yet come.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1341
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then said Jesus again unto them, I go my way, and ye shall seek me, and shall die in your sins: whither I go, ye cannot come.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moro. 10:26 (24\u201326). TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then said the Jews, Will he kill himself? because he saith, Whither I go, ye cannot come.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he said unto them, Ye are from beneath; I am from above: ye are of this world; I am not of this world.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 3:31 (13, 31).",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0World.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I said therefore unto you, that ye shall die in your sins: for if ye believe not that I am he, ye shall die in your sins.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 138:32 (31\u201334).",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Faith.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Then said they unto him, Who art thou? And Jesus saith unto them, Even the same that I said unto you from the beginning.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I have many things to say and to judge of you: but he that sent me is true; and I speak to the world those things which I have heard of him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Revelation.",
                        "start": 127,
                        "end": 132
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They understood not that he spake to them of the Father.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then said Jesus unto them, When ye have lifted up the Son of man, then shall ye know that I am he, and that I do nothing of myself; but as my Father hath taught me, I speak these things.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 5:19.",
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 120
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 7:16 (16\u201318). TG\u00a0Authority.",
                        "start": 142,
                        "end": 148
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Delegation of Responsibility.",
                        "start": 154,
                        "end": 160
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 18:18.",
                        "start": 167,
                        "end": 172
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 98
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And he that sent me is with me: the Father hath not left me alone; for I do always those things that please him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Authority of.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 8:16; 16:32. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Relationships with the Father.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 65
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Obedience.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 4:34.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "As he spake these words, many believed on him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 12:42 (11, 42).",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then said Jesus to those Jews which believed on him, If ye continue in my word, then are ye my disciples indeed;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Commitment; Perseverance; Steadfastness.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 27:57.",
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And ye shall know the truth, and the truth shall make you free.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Conversion; Testimony.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 50:25. TG\u00a0Education; Gospel; Truth.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moro. 10:5.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 21:4. TG\u00a0Bondage, Spiritual; Liberty.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They answered him, We be Abraham's seed, and were never in bondage to any man: how sayest thou, Ye shall be made free?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Abrahamic Covenant.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Jesus answered them, Verily, verily, I say unto you, Whosoever committeth sin is the servant of sin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 29:40.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 6:16; Alma 12:11 (9\u201311, 17). TG\u00a0Servant.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the servant abideth not in the house for ever: but the Son abideth ever.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "If the Son therefore shall make you free, ye shall be free indeed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Bondage, Spiritual; Liberty.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I know that ye are Abraham's seed; but ye seek to kill me, because my word hath no place in you.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I speak that which I have seen with my Father: and ye do that which ye have seen with your father.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They answered and said unto him, Abraham is our father. Jesus saith unto them, If ye were Abraham's children, ye would do the works of Abraham.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Abrahamic Covenant.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 99
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Seed of Abraham.",
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 108
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Good Works.",
                        "start": 126,
                        "end": 131
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But now ye seek to kill me, a man that hath told you the truth, which I have heard of God: this did not Abraham.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye do the deeds of your father. Then said they to him, We be not born of fornication; we have one Father, even God.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 106,
                        "end": 110
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Jesus said unto them, If God were your Father, ye would love me: for I proceeded forth and came from God; neither came I of myself, but he sent me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 16:28 (27\u201328, 30); 17:8; Gal. 4:4.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 95
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Messenger of the Covenant.",
                        "start": 139,
                        "end": 143
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1342
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Why do ye not understand my speech? even because ye cannot hear my word.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0John 8:43 \u2026 bear\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye are of your father the devil, and the lusts of your father ye will do. He was a murderer from the beginning, and abode not in the truth, because there is no truth in him. When he speaketh a lie, he speaketh of his own: for he is a liar, and the father of it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Jn. 3:10 (10\u201318). TG\u00a0Devil; Devil, Church of.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Lust.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Murder.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 91
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Truth.",
                        "start": 133,
                        "end": 138
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Lying.",
                        "start": 193,
                        "end": 196
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Honesty.",
                        "start": 234,
                        "end": 238
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And because I tell you the truth, ye believe me not.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Which of you convinceth me of sin? And if I say the truth, why do ye not believe me?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0convicts, reproves.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Heb. 4:15.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that is of God heareth God's words: ye therefore hear them not, because ye are not of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0John 8:47 He that is of God receiveth God's words; ye therefore receive them not, because ye are not of God.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Dan. 12:10; 1\u00a0Jn. 4:6 (5\u20136); 2\u00a0Ne. 33:10 (10\u201311).",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Then answered the Jews, and said unto him, Say we not well that thou art a Samaritan, and hast a devil?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 3:9.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Jesus answered, I have not a devil; but I honour my Father, and ye do dishonour me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, the Standard of Righteousness; Honoring Father and Mother; Respect.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I seek not mine own glory: there is one that seeketh and judgeth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 7:18.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Verily, verily, I say unto you, If a man keep my saying, he shall never see death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 5:24; 11:26; D&C 63:49. TG\u00a0Death, Spiritual, First; Death, Spiritual, Second.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then said the Jews unto him, Now we know that thou hast a devil. Abraham is dead, and the prophets; and thou sayest, If a man keep my saying, he shall never taste of death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 42:46 (46\u201347).",
                        "start": 157,
                        "end": 162
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Art thou greater than our father Abraham, which is dead? and the prophets are dead: whom makest thou thyself?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Jesus answered, If I honour myself, my honour is nothing: it is my Father that honoureth me; of whom ye say, that he is your God:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Body of, Corporeal Nature.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Honor.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yet ye have not known him; but I know him: and if I should say, I know him not, I shall be a liar like unto you: but I know him, and keep his saying.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Your father Abraham rejoiced to see my day: and he saw it, and was glad.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 22:8 (8\u201314); Hel. 8:17 (16\u201319).",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
